-- Alstom SA, Banco Santander, Bayer, Grifols, Neopost: Europe Equity Preview
-- B y   E l i z a b e t h   S t a n t o n
-- 2010-09-29T04:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/banco-santander-bayer-grifols-neopost-europe-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in  European  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are from the last close.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index  fell 0.2 percent to $262.36. The
 Stoxx 50 Index  slid 0.4 percent to 2,517.24. The  Euro Stoxx 50
Index , a benchmark for nations using the euro, dropped 0.1
percent to 2,774.62.  Alstom SA  (ALO FP): The French engineering group joined
Polish construction company PBG SA and Polish engineering group
Rafako SA in a bid to build two new 900-megawatt generation
units at Polska Grupa Energetyczna SA’s Opole power plant. The
stock rose 1.1 percent to 37.12 euros.  Banco Comercial Portugues SA  (BCP PL): Sonangol EP,
Angola’s state-owned oil company, increased its stake in
Portugal’s biggest publicly traded bank by assets to 10.168
percent, the lender said. BCP shares declined 0.2 percent to 63
euro cents.  Banco Santander SA  (SAN SM): Spain’s biggest bank was
raised to “Buy” from “Hold” at Independent Research GmbH by
equity analyst Matthias Engelmayer, who expects the stock to
reach 11 euros a share in six months. The shares fell 0.5
percent to 9.33 euros.  Bayer AG  (BAYN GY): The U.S. Supreme Court agreed to
consider reviving a bid by two West Virginians to press a class-
action suit against a unit of the company over its withdrawn
cholesterol drug Baycol. The shares rose less than 0.1 percent
to 51.98 euros.  Eurazeo SA  (RF FP): France’s largest publicly traded
private equity firm completed the sale of its stake in B&B
Hotels Group to the Carlyle Group. The sale will generate
proceeds of 184 million euros. The shares rose 2.5 percent to
48.79 euros.  Grifols SA  (GRF SQ):  Europe’s largest maker of blood-
plasma products cut the interest rate it will pay on $1.6
billion of term loans to fund its purchase of Talecris
Biotherapeutics Holdings Corp., according to a person familiar
with the transaction. The shares rose 0.8 percent to 10.93
euros.  Neopost SA  (NEO FP): Europe’s biggest maker of mailroom
equipment said first-half net income fell to 70.9 million euros
from 74.8 million euros a year earlier. The shares fell less
than 0.1 percent to 55.48 euros.  Renault SA  (RNO FP): RCI Banque SA, the financing arm of
the French carmaker, canceled its sale of five-year bonds in
euros. The shares fell 1.7 percent to 36.90 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
